# 2603 spectra of 462 type Ia supernovae published by Blondin et al.
#
#      "The Spectroscopic Diversity of Type Ia Supernovae"
#
# accepted for publication in AJ



#VERSION: cfaspec_snIa_20120322.tar.gz



############################
# GENERAL INFORMATION
############################

The spectra (*.flm) are organized in subdirectories, one per
supernova. The file naming convention for each spectrum is:

   <SN name>-<UT date>-<tel/inst>.flm

   SN name : supernova name (e.g., sn2008bf)
   UT date : UT date at midpoint of observations, YYYYMMDD.dd format
   tel/inst: name of telescope or instrument; choices are:

   	     fast : FLWO 1.5m+FAST
	     mmt  : MMT 6.5m+Blue/Red Channel
	     ldss2: Magellan Clay 6.5m+LDSS2
	     ldss3: Magellan Clay 6.5m+LDSS3
	     imacs: Magellan Baade 6.5m+IMACS

The spectra are all in three-column ascii format:

1st column = *observed* wavelength (units = Angstroems [A])
2nd column = *observed* flux (units = erg/s/cm^2/A)
3rd column = flux error (one sigma; units = erg/s/cm^2/A)

NOTES: 

(1) the flux error is computed based on the optimal extraction
    algorithm of Horne (1986). Several spectra have no error
    information, in which case the flux error is set to 0.0
    everywhere.

(2) no attempt has been made to scale the spectra to match the
    available photometry.

(3) the observed wavelength includes a heliocentric correction.


====> THE SPECTRA HAVE *NOT* BEEN DE-REDSHIFTED OR DE-REDDENED <====


Other files are also included:

cfaspec_snIa.pdf - single document containing plots of all the spectra
cfaspec_snIa_obstable.pdf - journal of observations
cfasnIa_param.dat - table giving basic SN parameters
cfasnIa_mjdspec.dat - table giving MJD of each spectrum
branchwangclass.dat - table with measurements used to classify SNIa into 
                      the subclasses defined by Branch et al. (2006) and 
		      Wang et al. (2009b)



